## Vintage Yellow Gold Pear Diamond Ring

The Vintage Convergence makes the pear diamond the most period-correct stone shape for a vintage yellow gold ring. Pear cuts appear throughout Victorian estate jewelry from 1860–1900 and in the Edwardian period (1901–1910) alongside milgrain, filigree, and hand-engraving in yellow gold and silver-topped yellow gold constructions.

For **authentic vintage pieces**, search estate jewelers, Christie's and Sotheby's jewelry auctions, and specialist retailers like Erstwhile or Doyle & Doyle. Original Victorian pear diamonds in yellow gold mounts often feature old mine or old European cutting styles — hand-cut stones with slightly different facet geometry than modern GIA Ideal cut. Each is unique.

