## Wedding Band Pairing for a Yellow Gold Pear Diamond Ring

The pear diamond creates a specific band challenge: its curved belly does not sit flush against a standard straight band, leaving a visible gap between the two rings.

**Three solutions that work:**

**Contoured yellow gold band:** A band shaped to mirror the pear belly, sitting flush against the stone. This is the cleanest solution. Most jewelers can fabricate a custom contoured band; it typically adds $400–$800 to the band cost. Match the karatage exactly — 14k engagement ring with 14k band. Mismatched gold tones are visible in yellow gold in a way they are not in platinum.

**Straight band with deliberate gap:** Some buyers choose a thin (1.5–2mm) plain yellow gold band and accept a small visual gap as a design choice rather than a flaw. In warm gold, the gap reads intentional and modern. This works best with a point-up oriented pear.

**Stacked bands on the outer side:** Two thin yellow gold bands flanking the pear ring on either side of the finger — one toward the hand, one toward the nail — creates a balanced, decorative frame without any gap concern.

[![Yellow gold pear diamond ring with wedding band pairing](/images/bn-yg-pear-ring-6.avif)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=yg&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Pear&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

